    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A general comment: As a hack, this is okay. However, I wouldn't use Javascript to fix things that are supposed to be done in pure CSS.\n\n@Carreau \n\nWhen I was writing the PR for a fixed header, I noticed that `position: sticky;` doesn't really work as a replacement of `position: fixed;` at least without a careful consideration of the layout.  `sticky` has the effect of hiding the header when the parent no longer fits the page. Since the browser support is not good at all, I didn't look deep enough to make it work. However, let's say it doesn't work \"out of the box\".\n"
  },
