    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Here are some comments from our discussion at the weekly devmeeting:\n- We do want to fix this behavior\n- We feel that the implementation in this PR is too hackish\n- When we moving to phosphor all of this will be handled differently, but...\n- We are open to a clean implementation of this for 4.0 (pre-phosphor).\n\nOur thoughts on a clean implementation:\n- The entire dashboard page wouldn't scroll, just the dev that has the list in each of the 3 tabs.\n- The affixed content will be outside that scrolling div so you get the desired behavior for free.\n- We may need to refactor the main page template to get this behavior without affecting the other pages (terminal, text editor, notebook).\n"
